The paper introduces an entity-centric search engine that aggregates articles and comments from various sources, performs sentiment analysis, and mines for temporal trends and insights. This involves natural language processing, information retrieval, and data mining techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD), and Cybersecurity (cs.CY). However, since the paper does not focus on any specific sub-topic within these areas, it could also be relevant to other sub-categories such as Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
